    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen an lsp is loading, use `lua vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(0, { force = true })` to delete the buffer, and the following error will appear:\r\n```\r\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: ...ed-nightly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inlay_hint.lua:73: Invalid buffer id: 17\r\n\r\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: ...ghtly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:309: ...ghtly/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:102: Invalid buffer id: 26\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open a buffer and load lsp (choose the one with longer loading time)\r\n1. Execute `:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(0, { force = true })`\r\n1. An error will be thrown\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nat [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/b3d94b10870ce494941279f78387e1d98a7e48e7/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/inlay_hint.lua#L73C3-L73C60) place:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal lines = api.nvim_buf_get_lines(bufnr, 0, -1, false)\r\n```\r\nMaybe we can use `vim.api.nvim_buf_is_valid` before calling `api.nvim_buf_get_lines` to check whether the buffer is still valid at this time\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.11.0-nightly+3c53e8f\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 11 WSL2 nixos\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nWezterm\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnix package",
